@echo off

:: ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
:: TCC-RT Unit Test Runner [triangle.btm]
:: Anthony J. Borla (ajborla@bigpond.com)
:: ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

call TCCUNIT << "EOF"
"All sides are equal, equilateral" EQ 0 true triangle equilateral 2 2 2
"Any side is unequal" EQ 0 false triangle equilateral 2 3 2
"No sides are equal, equilateral" EQ 0 false triangle equilateral 5 4 6
"All zero sides is not a triangle" EQ 0 false triangle equilateral 0 0 0
"Sides may be floats, equilateral" EQ 0 true triangle equilateral 0.5 0.5 0.5
"Last two sides are equal" EQ 0 true triangle isosceles 3 4 4
"First two sides are equal" EQ 0 true triangle isosceles 4 4 3
"First and last sides are equal" EQ 0 true triangle isosceles 4 3 4
"Equilateral triangles are also isosceles" EQ 0 true triangle isosceles 4 4 4
"No sides are equal, isosceles" EQ 0 false triangle isosceles 2 3 4
"First triangle inequality violation" EQ 0 false triangle isosceles 1 1 3
"Second triangle inequality violation" EQ 0 false triangle isosceles 1 3 1
"Third triangle inequality violation" EQ 0 false triangle isosceles 3 1 1
"Sides may be floats, isosceles" EQ 0 true triangle isosceles 0.5 0.4 0.5
"No sides are equal, scalene" EQ 0 true triangle scalene 5 4 6
"All sides are equal, scalene" EQ 0 false triangle scalene 4 4 4
"First and second sides are equal" EQ 0 false triangle scalene 4 4 3
"First and third sides are equal" EQ 0 false triangle scalene 3 4 3
"Second and third sides are equal" EQ 0 false triangle scalene 4 3 3
"May not violate triangle inequality" EQ 0 false triangle scalene 7 3 2
"Sides may be floats, scalene" EQ 0 true triangle scalene 0.5 0.4 0.6
"No input should return an error" EQ 1 "ERROR: Invalid arguments. USAGE: triangle equilateral^|isosceles^|scalene A B C" triangle
"Too many arguments should return an error" EQ 1 "ERROR: Invalid arguments. USAGE: triangle equilateral^|isosceles^|scalene A B C" triangle 16 45 66 34 56
"Unrecognized triangle type should return an error" EQ 1 "ERROR: Invalid triangle type. USAGE: triangle equilateral^|isosceles^|scalene A B C" triangle total 10 3 6
"Alpha input should return an error" EQ 1 "ERROR: Only numeric values allowed. USAGE: triangle equilateral^|isosceles^|scalene A B C" triangle isosceles "abcd" 5 7
EOF

